programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Song of the Wild West
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a young country singer who is hoping to follow in her mother's footsteps. Next, they help a widow mourning her late husband.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: One Fresh Batch of Lemonade - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan must find a way to help Deke, a college football star whose dreams of reaching the pros are shattered by a tragic motorcycle accident.
programme.sub-title: One Fresh Batch of Lemonade - Part 1

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Soccer Mom to Soccer Bomb!
programme.desc: Colleen Radcliffe is a mother of four and says she doesn't have a spare second to spend on herself. Colleen feels like the old mom with no end in sight, but we're here to teach her that isn't the case. Time to make Colleen look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Photo-phobic To Photogenic
programme.desc: After a rough divorce, Alison has became a single mom. The stress of being the sole breadwinner has left its mark. Will the experts be able to give Alison back her youthful glow?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Spinning a More Youthful Look
programme.desc: Evan is a mobile DJ who is trying to take his business to the next level. Evan hasn't had the time or money to take care his looks but he knows it's absolutely necessary now if his business is going to continue growing.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Getting Back on the Catwalk
programme.desc: Stacey is a former model whose appearance has gone downhill because of the demands of caring for both her new baby and her ill mother. She's eager to get back on the catwalk and our team of experts will do a head to toe transformation.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Ronnie Donno
programme.desc: Teaching assistant Ronnie Donno already feels bad about the way she looks but before work can begin on getting her to look younger she has to hear how old 100 members of the public think she looks.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jackie Ralph
programme.desc: Inside, Jackie Ralph still feels like a flirty young woman. Only problem is, she's trapped inside the body of a 61 year old – at least that's what the British public think. Nicky Hambleton Jones and her team of experts take charge.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep
programme.desc: Tracy is a dedicated single mom, and a survivor. After devastating cystic acne scarred her face, she suffered a terrible oven accident that left her with even more scars. Our team of experts, and The Glam Squad, give Tracy the TLC she deserves
programme.sub-title: Beauty is More Than Skin Deep

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Polishing the Prize
programme.desc: Ellisa is a recent newlywed whose life hasn't felt much like a honeymoon since her husband is always on the road for work and she is left at home with a new baby! Fearing that her husband could stray while away, our team of experts help Ellisa.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand
programme.desc: Everyone wants to look younger but if you work hard and play hard like Sue Whyte, it's far tougher to roll back those years. Sue's already stopped smoking and lost a lot of weight so can Fiona McDonald and her team of time warriors take care of the rest?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Pain No Gain
programme.desc: Once a sun-worshipping fashion model, Linda led a charmed life of good looks. After the devastating loss of her family, life became difficult. Linda is willing to do anything to recover her former looks and finds out that beauty comes with a price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back
programme.desc: In her youth, Catherine was a wild child punk rocker whose bright red mohawk got her elected homecoming queen. But now that Catherine is a single mother of twin teenage daughters, she feels like she's lost her young, eye-catching style.
programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Guilty Of Needing A Makeover
programme.desc: After a career as a cop and a private investigator, Lita worked her way through law school while raising her son. She's finished school and taken the bar exam, but her face and body have paid the price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Prepping For The Big Day
programme.desc: Lilia is the first in her family to finish college. She helps support her family and bought a house she shares with her mother. Her achievements have carried a price; she looks old and tired compared to her friends.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A New Look On Life
programme.desc: At one time Trisha was a golden locked, free-spirited surfer, but once she settled down and had children her looks and self-esteem took a downward spiral. Suddenly single again, Trisha needs help searching for her energetic youth.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 8
programme.desc: Caroline returns to find that all is not well at Leopard's Den. Danny has been putting a brave face on his ban but his attempts at helping out around the house are getting on everyone's nerves and Alice is finding his back-seat vetting especially hard.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: Danny is delighted to have his veterinary license back again and being back at work is helping to distract him from the impending anniversary of Sarah's death.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Du Plessis is restless after his heart surgery but the family insist he needs to relax. Meanwhile Danny and Alice are happy to have closed down a zoo down that has been mistreating animals.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: While on honeymoon in London, Alice discovers that Danny has some final business to do before they can return home to Africa. He's reluctantly arranged to meet his estranged father, Robert, who has recently got back in touch.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny is throwing himself into his work after the death of his father, and has applied for the role of State Vet. However, Danny's attempts to involve Thabo in the first phase of the Lion Breeding Project lead to Du Plessis feeling like an outsider.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: It is Danny's first day as State Vet and when he helps rescue some smuggled animals he feels he's making a difference. However, he discovers the role isn't going to be all plain sailing.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny's first big project as State Vet is a major animal translocation, and he is desperate to impress. Meanwhile, whilst Alice is out in the bush treating an injured zebra, she is stalked by lions. She makes it back to her jeep in time but is shaken up.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Alice is still suffering from a loss of nerve after her close shave with the lions and so Danny tries to help her overcome her problems – the Leopard's Den lions have produced their first cub and he needs Alice back in the saddle.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: A 39 year old man has crashed his bike 15 kilometres south of Auckland city and an elderly man has collapsed while walking. He is unable to speak properly and is incorreherent at Waiheke Island.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggle to save a Paeroa farmer.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: Tropical rain has hit Wellsford, flooding the entire town and leaving a pregnant woman and her unborn child fighting for their lives.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: An 11-year-old girl has ended up under an overturned boat.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: A Glenbrook farmer has been left seriously injured after one of his Highland cows has taken to him with its horns.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The team are being sent out to a traumatic accident that will end up being rather close to home.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Rescue chopper team is en route to Whitianga to help save a badly injured stock car driver.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper team are about to take off to rescue a seriously injured man.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper team is responding to a life threatening emergency.

programme.title: Sports Cars: Chevrolet / Kia

programme.title: Sports Cars: Lamborghini

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Hiker Robert had trained for over 6 months for the remote Cradle Mountain bush walk. With his young daughter in tow they set off on a 48 km walk. Three hours into the walk Roberts health takes a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12
programme.desc: The team are called out to a status 2 emergency; Clark Chamberlain was abseiling when he fell from the top of a cliff to the ground. He's now in a critical condition suffering from multiple injuries.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 13
programme.desc: The team are responding to reports of a life-or death emergency; Jim Te Whata has been pulled from the water cold, unconscious and not breathing.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Highfall
programme.desc: While most people never had a car crash, they know spectacular car crashes with huge explosions from movies. But these scenes are much more sensational than in real life, because cars hardly ever explode.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are tough professionals. They jump from houses and make cars fly or explode. On this episode, reporter Dean Malay takes a look behind the scenes of the stunt company.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Bike stunts
programme.desc: This time the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept deal with motorbike stunts: high jumps, risky drops and dangerous crashes. As usual, stunt coordinator Domi requires his motorbike specialists Daniel and Marcel to be in top form.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Ambulance
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are always looking for new spectacular stunts and are not running out of options. Stunt coordinator Domi’s latest idea involves an old ambulance.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Matrix

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Multiple Collision

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The White Army

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Alarm in the Ski Resort
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are still at their ski resort and party hard. This time they prepared a spectacular stunt involving a station wagon. It is thrown 50 meters into the air with a cannon.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Body Stunt Highlights
